        1. Do some research to see what other data scientists are making near you. Location can impact your salary. Those in big cities may make more than those in smaller towns.

        3. Make a note of skills you have that are in demand for data scientists, like analytical skills, critical and logical thinking, math expertise, and fluency in programs like Python, R, and SQL.
